Enum MesosferQuery.CachePolicy

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<MesosferQuery.CachePolicy>
      • com.mesosfer.MesosferQuery.CachePolicy
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<MesosferQuery.CachePolicy>
    Enclosing class:
    MesosferQuery<T extends MesosferObject>

    public static enum MesosferQuery.CachePolicy
extends Enum<MesosferQuery.CachePolicy>
    CachePolicy specifies different caching policies that could be used with MesosferQuery.

    This lets you show data when the user's device is offline, or when the app has just started and network requests have not yet had time to complete. Mesosfer takes care of automatically flushing the cache when it takes up too much space.

    Note: Cache policy can only be set when Local Datastore is not enabled.

    See Also:
    MesosferQuery

      The query first loads from the cache, then loads from the network.
      IGNORE_CACHE
      The query does not load from the cache or save results to the cache.
      NETWORK_ELSE_CACHE
      The query first tries to load from the network, but if that fails, it loads results from the cache.
      NETWORK_ONLY
      The query does not load from the cache, but it will save results to the cache.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • IGNORE_CACHE

        public static final MesosferQuery.CachePolicy IGNORE_CACHE
        The query does not load from the cache or save results to the cache.

        This is the default cache policy.

      • CACHE_ONLY

        public static final MesosferQuery.CachePolicy CACHE_ONLY
        The query only loads from the cache, ignoring the network.

        If there are no cached results, this causes a MesosferException.CACHE_MISS.

      • NETWORK_ONLY

        public static final MesosferQuery.CachePolicy NETWORK_ONLY
        The query does not load from the cache, but it will save results to the cache.

      • CACHE_ELSE_NETWORK

        public static final MesosferQuery.CachePolicy CACHE_ELSE_NETWORK
        The query first tries to load from the cache, but if that fails, it loads results from the network.

        If there are no cached results, this causes a MesosferException.CACHE_MISS.

      • NETWORK_ELSE_CACHE

        public static final MesosferQuery.CachePolicy NETWORK_ELSE_CACHE
        The query first tries to load from the network, but if that fails, it loads results from the cache.

        If there are no cached results, this causes a MesosferException.CACHE_MISS.

      • CACHE_THEN_NETWORK

        public static final MesosferQuery.CachePolicy CACHE_THEN_NETWORK
        The query first loads from the cache, then loads from the network. The callback will be called twice - first with the cached results, then with the network results. Since it returns two results at different times, this cache policy cannot be used with synchronous or task methods.
